  "story": "An exuberant praise hymn that has been a hallmark of Telugu Christian worship for over a century. The word 'Hallelujah' combined with 'Sthothram' (praise/thanks) creates a powerful expression of worship. This keerthanamu is often sung with great energy and clapping in both traditional and charismatic Telugu churches.",
